data.description: Get away to your own Montana farmhouse on 7.5 acres. Look over your fenced meadow, as the horses graze in the pasture, with the Swan Mountains in the background. You'll find pleasant evening shade from the tall, mature pines and a Weeping Willow. To the north, you see the many newly planted fruit trees in the meadow and the cut slopes of Whitefish Mountain Resort. Traffic is a bit slower on this serene country road. The coveted Trumbull Meadows is centrally located in the valley. You're only minutes from the airport, Costco, skiing, lakes, rivers, fine dining and the Crown of the Continent, which is Glacier National Park. This newly painted and remodeled 5 bed/3 bath Montana home is large enough to fit your family and entertain your friends. With a massive deck and covered porch, there is room enough for everyone. The high-bay detached garage and shop is the perfect getaway location for all those projects that need to get done!
